      "message": "I thought I had answered this before but my reply seems to go lost:\nthe Generated code uses these variable names (in the interface and in the base impl. class) \n\nI agree it is inconsistent with our general naming convention but I think we need to follow the parent set by Antlr itself here I think. One of the advantages (and maybe the reason they did this) that one often refactor/renames rules. use the same name for the ctx variable makes it easier to move code to new rules due to this refactoring etc,",
